<% content_for :head do %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag "koi/nav_items" %>
<% end %>

<% content_for :title, "Sitemap" %>

<div class="sitemap application" data-uri-save="<%= koi_engine.savesort_nav_items_path %>">
  <ol>
    <%= render 'nav_item', nav_item: NavItem.root, level: 0 %>
  </ol>
</div>

<div id="modal-for-nav-item">&nbsp;</div>

<% content_for :side do %>

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Adding a page</h2>
    
    <p>To select a new page move your cursor over the item above or the folder the page should be part of. Roll over the 'add' link and select 'page' to add the page. </p>
    <p>After you have added the page, go back to the site map and move the page to the correct position.</p>
    <p>More information can be found in the <%= link_to "help section", koi_engine.help_path %>.</p>

    <p>To add a new page hover your mouse over the page or the folder (suitcase icon) which the new page should be a part of. The selected page or folder should be highlighted in grey. Roll over the menu items on the right until you reach ‘ADD’. In the drop down menu select ‘page’. Begin adding content to your new page.</p>

    <p>After you have added content to your new page, hit ’Save’ to create it on the Sitemap. Once saved, you will be taken back to the Sitemap where you can move the new page to its correct position. Your new page will always be at the bottom of the list of the page or folder which you added to.</p>

<!--
    <p>Note: if you cannot move pages up or down you may need to ‘Enable drag and drop’ located above this message.</p>
-->

    <p>To view a demonstration video please go to the help section.</p>

  </div>

<% end %>

